Jan 12 2009 	Good Location and Value	I spent the entire month of November at the Jianguo Hotel. I was in a non-smoking room on the third floor of Building A. While I believe the entire floor was non-smoking, the room had a residual smoke smell that I was able to dissapate by leaving with window open about six inches. The room was on the backside of the hotel and faced apartment buildings. I found the room to be clean and the maid service thorough. The bed was comfortable, though I would have liked a foam pillow option. I've stayed at five other hotels during trips to Beijing and, in my opinion, the breakfast here is by far the best of the lot. In summary, there was nothing all that outstanding or all that bad about the hotel. It was very servicable, reasonably priced and, as a result, a good value.I do disagree with the reviewer who suggested using a taxi versus taking the subway. There's no blanket solution to this issue. It depends on where you are going and the time of day you are traveling. If your destination is close to a subway stop and it's at a time of day when traffic is gridlocked, you'll arrive much quicker on the subway than in a taxi.	
