Dec 2 2007	Great Alternative Hotel in the World Trade Center Area...	Just wrapped up my 20th trip to Beijing and have stayed at hotels in all areas of the city. I stayed at this hotel about 8 years ago and wasn't overly thrilled then but gave it another try last week given all other hotels in the area had no suites left. Overall, this is a great alternative hotel choice for Beijing that, for the price makes this comparable to any other hotel.Pro's* This is a smaller hotel thus not all of the noise and lack of service that I have experienced so many times in other large hotels (namely the Hyatt and China World hotels where there are simply too many guests for the hotel to service them all). Also, very easy to get in and out of this hotel without the hassles of a massive lobby or requring a key card to use the elevator.* Recently renovated rooms. I stayed in a suite in the B wing of the hotel, bed was comfortable, room was clean and no noise at night. Pictures attached to this review.* Price - this suite was 1/2 the price of the comparable suite at any hotel in the area (China World, Kerry Centre) and I can say that the experience certainly did not reflect a lesser price.* Experience with foreigners. This hotel was absolutely full of foreigners -- americans and europeans; tourists and businessmen alike. Everyone in the hotel spoke English. Con* A smaller hotel may not appeal to some; this hotel lacks the pomp and size of the large hotels. People on this site seem enamored with the large hotels like Hyatt and China World Hotel despite the terrible service in these hotels.	
